## Temporary Access Pass (TAP)

A TAP is a time-limited one-time code generated by an IT 
admin. Used when:
- New starter hasn't set up MFA yet
- User lost their phone
- User is locked out

### TAP Generated for Alex Johnson
- Code: [redacted for security]
- Valid: 1 hour
- One-time use: Yes
- Registration URL: https://aka.ms/mysecurityinfo

### TAP Workflow
1. Admin generates TAP in Entra ID
2. Admin securely sends code to user
3. User goes to aka.ms/mysecurityinfo
4. User enters TAP instead of password
5. User registers Microsoft Authenticator
6. TAP expires — Authenticator becomes their MFA method

---

## Key Admin Actions

| Action | When to use |
|---|---|
| Generate TAP | User lost phone or new starter |
| Require re-register MFA | User gets new phone |
| Revoke sessions | Account compromised — kick out immediately |
| Reset password | User forgot password |

